article.description: — Earl Timberlake's 26 points helped Bryant defeat University of Albany 98-89 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Timberlake scores 26 to help Bryant earn 98-89 win over Albany
article.linkText: Timberlake scores 26 to help Bryant earn 98-89 win over Albany
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Earl Timberlake's 26 points helped Bryant defeat University of Albany 98-89 on Saturday night. Timberlake added nine rebounds for the Bulldogs (12-7, 4-0 America East Conference). Sherif Gross-Bullock scored 21 points and added five rebounds. Daniel Rivera shot 7 of 7 from the field and 0 for 5 from the line to finish with 14 points, while adding nine rebounds, five assists, four steals, and five blocks. The Great Danes (10-9, 2-2) were led in scoring by Amar'e Marshall, who finished with 26 points and five assists. Sebastian Thomas added 20 points for Albany (NY). In addition, Ny'Mire Little finished with 12 points and four steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
